body:
I tried to reproduce this issue, but with the code below, I was able to extract the zip file generated with zip4j. 

```
@Test
public void testIssueAdd() throws IOException {
  File fileToAdd = new File(BASE_DIR + "123.pdf");
  ZipParameters zipParameters = new ZipParameters();
  zipParameters.setEncryptFiles(true);
  zipParameters.setEncryptionMethod(EncryptionMethod.ZIP_STANDARD);
  new ZipFile(BASE_DIR + "test.zip", "你好".toCharArray()).addFile(fileToAdd, zipParameters);

  ZipFile zipFile = new ZipFile(BASE_DIR + "test.zip", "你好".toCharArray());
  zipFile.extractAll(BASE_DIR);
}
```

I tried with `ZIP_STANDARD` as well as `AES` and both worked fine. I was not able to extract the zip file you attached, but I cannot say why that is not working. But Chinese passwords should work with zip4j. I think there are also integration tests to verify them. The only difference is that I used the latest code (v2.6.4).
